A Tringa stagnatilis is a small wader bird.
It has a distinct white eyebrow and a dark stripe through its eye.
Its back and wings are a mottled brown color.
The chest and belly are white, while the legs are a yellowish-green hue.
Tringa stagnatilis are commonly found near freshwater sources such as ponds and streams.
They are known to migrate long distances across Europe and Asia.
Their diet primarily consists of small invertebrates such as insects and crustaceans.
